      "content": "Wait, \"slightly more modest\"? A 25% increase? I just looked at the raw statistical significance tables in the draft report, and the p-value for the primary endpoint across the entire population is 0.08. That's not a success, that's a failure to reach significance. If I tell the board we \"met the primary endpoint\" when the data shows we didn't, they're going to tear us apart during the audit. Why did you say the endpoint was met?",
